{% import "./m_pageTitle.pattern" as pattern %}
{% import "../m_patternBlock/m_patternBlock.pattern" as block %}

{% set d %}
{% markdown %}
`m_pageTitle` renders the main page title `h1` with an optional `time` tag for dates. One one should be used per page. Passing only a title string will render a `h1`. The first letter is automatically capitalised.
{% endmarkdown %}
{% endset %}

{{ block.m_patternBlock(d,'pattern.m_pageTitle(\'jedi mind tricks\')') }}
{{pattern.m_pageTitle('jedi mind tricks')}}

{% set d %}
{% markdown %}
`m_pageTitle` can also be passed an optional date attribute. A date should be passed in ISO format, this is then transcoded into a human readable date.
{% endmarkdown %}
{% endset %}
{{ block.m_patternBlock(d, 'pattern.m_pageTitle(\'jedi mind tricks\',\'20160504\')')}}
{{pattern.m_pageTitle('jedi mind tricks','20160504')}}
